rComments: Very nice and helpful prof! She was very clear and helpful for office hours.
A very good professor, knows her stuff!! Easy to approach and talk too.  Her tests are medium, just study notes the text and you'll be fine.

Very passionate about what she teaches. She is a good speaker and information from lectures matches the text book. Exams were hard but the written papers saved my mark. Attending lectures are not necessary but reading the textbook is a must.
When you have to write a paper, do not worry about the quality of your writing or a unique idea, just regurgitate as much information she taught you as possible.

One of the most comprehensible professors I have ever had. Very clear. Exams reflect course material very well and are quite easy if you read the texts and attend class. I would recommend this class and this prof to anyone who wants to bring up their GPA and learn more about how complicated Christianity really is!
